{"name": "odoo14-addon-edi-state-oca", "metadata": {"name": "odoo14-addon-edi-state-oca", "version": "14.0.1.0.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Framework :: Odoo", "Framework :: Odoo :: 14.0", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Lesser General Public License v3 (LGPLv3)", "Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "https://github.com/OCA/edi-framework", "license": "LGPL-3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["odoo14-addon-edi-oca", "odoo"], "summary": "Allow to assign specific EDI states to related records.", "upload_time": 1698498920}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  badge1: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/maturity-Alpha-red.png\n    :alt: Alpha\n    :target: https://odoo-community.org/page/development-status\n    ```\n  badge2: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/licence-LGPL--3-blue.png\n    :alt: 'License: LGPL-3'\n    :target: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0-standalone.html\n    ```\n  badge3: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/github-OCA%2Fedi--framework-lightgray.png?logo=github\n    :alt: OCA/edi-framework\n    :target: https://github.com/OCA/edi-framework/tree/14.0/edi_state_oca\n    ```\n  badge4: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/weblate-Translate%20me-F47D42.png\n    :alt: Translate me on Weblate\n    :target: https://translation.odoo-community.org/projects/edi-framework-14-0/edi-framework-14-0-edi_state_oca\n    ```\n  badge5: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/runboat-Try%20me-875A7B.png\n    :alt: Try me on Runboat\n    :target: https://runboat.odoo-community.org/builds?repo=OCA/edi-framework&target_branch=14.0\n    ```\n  maintainer-simahawk: |-\n    ```{image} https://github.com/simahawk.png?size=40px\n    :alt: simahawk\n    :target: https://github.com/simahawk\n    ```\n---\n\n# EDI state\n\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n% !! This file is generated by oca-gen-addon-readme !!\n% !! changes will be overwritten.                   !!\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n% !! source digest: sha256:52a6e23022efc38b5cc56dc3153880410de7bf93615fd702c008d0e363a6cccf\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n\n{{ badge1 }} {{ badge2 }} {{ badge3 }} {{ badge4 }} {{ badge5 }}\n\nTechnical module for the EDI suite to provide additional states for any records.\n\nExample: a SO is generated via UBL file and you want to provide an ORDRSP with the right state on the order and on each line.\n\nIt provides 2 new models:\n\n- EDI state workflow\n\n  > - groups states together\n  > - limit states to a specific model\n\n- EDI state\n\n  > - describe the state of the record\n\n:::{IMPORTANT}\nThis is an alpha version, the data model and design can change at any time without warning.\nOnly for development or testing purpose, do not use in production.\n[More details on development status](https://odoo-community.org/page/development-status)\n:::\n\n**Table of contents**\n\n```{contents}\n:local: true\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nGo to \"EDI -> Config -> States\" and configure workflow and states.\nGo to \"EDI -> Config -> EDI Exchange Type\" and enable 1 or more workflow on a given type.\n\n## Usage\n\nAdd the mixin `edi.state.consumer.mixin` to the model that will use states.\n\n## Known issues / Roadmap\n\n- automatized state transitions (via domain and / or code snippet)\n\n## Bug Tracker\n\nBugs are tracked on [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/OCA/edi-framework/issues).\nIn case of trouble, please check there if your issue has already been reported.\nIf you spotted it first, help us to smash it by providing a detailed and welcomed\n[feedback](https://github.com/OCA/edi-framework/issues/new?body=module:%20edi_state_oca%0Aversion:%2014.0%0A%0A**Steps%20to%20reproduce**%0A-%20...%0A%0A**Current%20behavior**%0A%0A**Expected%20behavior**).\n\nDo not contact contributors directly about support or help with technical issues.\n\n## Credits\n\n### Authors\n\n- Camptocamp\n\n### Contributors\n\n- Simone Orsi \\<<mailto:simone.orsi@camptocamp.com>>\n\n### Maintainers\n\nThis module is maintained by the OCA.\n\n```{image} https://odoo-community.org/logo.png\n:alt: Odoo Community Association\n:target: https://odoo-community.org\n```\n\nOCA, or the Odoo Community Association, is a nonprofit organization whose\nmission is to support the collaborative development of Odoo features and\npromote its widespread use.\n\nCurrent [maintainer](https://odoo-community.org/page/maintainer-role):\n\n{{ maintainer-simahawk }}\n\nThis module is part of the [OCA/edi-framework](https://github.com/OCA/edi-framework/tree/14.0/edi_state_oca) project on GitHub.\n\nYou are welcome to contribute. To learn how please visit <https://odoo-community.org/page/Contribute>.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models.edi_exchange_type", "xref": {"fqname": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models..edi_exchange_type", "project": null}}, {"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models.edi_state", "xref": {"fqname": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models..edi_state", "project": null}}, {"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models.edi_state_consumer_mixin", "xref": {"fqname": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models..edi_state_consumer_mixin", "project": null}}, {"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models.edi_state_workflow", "xref": {"fqname": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models..edi_state_workflow", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models.edi_exchange_type", "documentation": ["Copyright 2023 Camptocamp SA", "@author Simone Orsi <simahawk@gmail.com>", "License LGPL-3.0 or later (http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl)."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models.edi_exchange_type.EDIExchangeType", "bases": ["models.Model"], "methods": [{"name": "odoo.addons.edi_state_oca.models.edi_exchang